\begin_layout Section
Hartree-Fock-Bogoliubov mean-field theory
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider an interacting many-body system of electrons described by the Hamiltoni
an
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
H & =H_{0}+H_{\text{int}}=\sum_{\alpha\beta}h_{\alpha\beta}c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}+\sum_{\alpha\beta\gamma\delta}V_{\gamma\delta}^{\alpha\beta}c_{\alpha}^{\dagger}c_{\beta}^{\dagger}c_{\gamma}c_{\delta},\label{eq:H}
\end{align}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $c^{\dagger}(c)$
\end_inset

 fermionic creation (annihilation) operators and the Greek indices 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha,\,\beta,\,\gamma,\,\delta$
\end_inset

 generic degrees of freedom.
 The time-dependency on the fermionic operators are being omitted for clarity,
 as is also done in the non-interacting Hamiltonian, accounting for a coupling
 to a perturbative external force, i.e 
\begin_inset Formula $h_{\alpha\beta}\rightarrow h_{\alpha\beta}+B_{\alpha\beta}F(t)$
\end_inset

.
 Concerning the interaction term, we assume 
\begin_inset Formula $V(\mathbf{r})$
\end_inset

 to be generic electrostatic potential of symmetry 
\begin_inset Formula $V(\mathbf{r}-\mathbf{r}^{\prime})=V(\mathbf{r}^{\prime}-\mathbf{r})$
\end_inset

 such that the interacting potential tensor has the symmetries 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{\gamma\delta}^{\alpha\beta}=V_{\delta\gamma}^{\beta\alpha}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(V_{\gamma\delta}^{\alpha\beta})^{*}=V_{\alpha\beta}^{\gamma\delta}$
\end_inset

.
